Almonem: a correction for the 111 anemonen.. The Almo was a small stream running into the Tiber just below the walls of Rome: the grotto which was built over its source is still in existence, containing the muti· lated image of the deity of the stream. The Almo is chiefly known in connexion with the worship of Cybele, whose image brought from Pessinus was lauded at its junction with the Tiber in no. 204, and was regularly washed there once a year, see Dict. of Geop. s v.
